Have the Python 3 +  pre-installed in your computer. 

Go to https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html and download the installer file for the python version.

Open the anaconda prompt :

To make sure that you are with the updated version 
Run:
(base) F:\> conda update -n base -c defaults conda

To create a conda environment with required tools
Run:
(base) F:\>mkdir AI

(base) F:\>cd AI

(base) F:\AI>conda create --prefix ./env pandas numpy matplotlib scikit-learn nltk scipy seaborn tensorflow keras Pillow plotly

To activate conda environment 
Run: 
(base) F:\AI>conda activate F:\AI\env

To isntall additional tools
Run: 
(F:\AI\env) F:\AI>conda install jupyter

To launch Jupyter Notebook for your project directory 

(F:\AI\env) F:\AI> jupyter notebook

If you experience Kernel error: kernel Unhandled error
from anaconda prompt 
(F:\AI\env) F:\AI>conda install pywin32
(F:\AI\env) F:\AI>pip install jupyter_client --upgrade

open an ipynb file to change the kernel
kernel->env 

If you experience FileNotFoundError: [WinError 2] and jupyter notebook doesnt work
FileNotFoundError: [WinError 2] The system cannot find the file specified

(f:\Academia\AI\env) F:\Academia\AI>python -m ipykernel install --user
Installed kernelspec python3 in C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Roaming\jupyter\kernels\python3

(f:\Academia\AI\env) F:\Academia\AI>jupyter notebook

open an ipynb file and use python3 as the kernel.

Note: Complete Step by step instructions with video tutorial for Mac, Windows and Linux is available at: 
